### Description

If I a either creating a new image or editing and existing file the SkBitmap.Encode method returns false.
The file that is created cannot be opened and is invalid or corrupt.

### Code

            SKImageInfo imageInfo = new SKImageInfo(1000, 800);
            using (SKBitmap bitmap = new SKBitmap(imageInfo))
            {
                SKCanvas canvas = new SKCanvas(bitmap);
                canvas.Clear(SKColors.White);

                using (SKWStream stream = new SKFileWStream("[File Path]"))
                {
                    bool results = bitmap.Encode(stream, SKEncodedImageFormat.Gif, 80);
                    // results are always false for GIF, ICO, WBMP
                }
            }

### Expected Behavior

The SkBitmap.Encode should return true and the file created\edited can be opened and viewed without issue.

### Actual Behavior

SkBitmap.Encode returns false and the file is corrupt\invalid.

### Basic Information

- Version with issue:  1.60.1
- Last known good version:  N\A
- IDE: VS2017
- Platform Target Frameworks: .NETstandard 2.0

- Target Devices: N\A (Library for use on several platforms)
